Program: Outlook
Title: 29/11/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00lqpdb
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 30 Nov 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world: Today, the Bangladeshi woman who had one of the shortest marriages in the world, asking for a divorce within minutes of her wedding, after the groom's family demanded a dowry. Also British film and tv star, Warwick Davis, who's just three feet six inches tall, talks about working in some of the biggest films in history, including Star Wars and Harry Potter. And the American man dedicated to snapping pictures of US post offices which are doomed to close. Show less